The legendary Countach's design concept is rooted in the changes that marked the 1970s, especially space missions. And today, we welcome @mauriziocheli, the world-famous Italian astronaut, to discuss how the automotive world and aerospace have inspired one another in the past decades.

#Lamborghini #CountachLegacy

This is Marcello Gandini, the pre-eminent automotive designer who pioneered the mold-breaking Super Sports Car Countach. 
When it was first launched in the 1970s, its angular and sharp design sparked controversy. Now it is considered a trailblazing achievement. 
Watch the exclusive video interview to discover more. 

#Lamborghini #Countach #CountachLegacy

Huracán Evo: fuel consumption combined 13.7 l/100km; CO2-emissions combined 332 g/km (WLTP)

#Lamborghini #AventadorSVJ63Roadster

This is the perfect meeting. Because Urus captures the Carrara marble's essence. Bold. Powerful. Smooth. And the Super SUV brings versatility to a new level. It merges sturdiness with elegance and is made for every surface even a marble quarry. Live an unprecedented driving experience. ​

Captured by @lucabracaliphotographer & @ernestomangone ​

#Lamborghini #Urus #UnlockAnyRoad 
__

Between tradition and innovation, Between craftsmanship and technology, between power and elegance. That's where Huracán EVO is poised. You can see it in its lines, the LDVI, and the premium lightweight materials used. But, without a shadow of a doubt, you can feel it when you're racing at 325 km/h.​

#Lamborghini #HuracanEVO #EveryDayAmplified ​

Captured by @s77kco for @lamborghini_birmingham

node.text:
The automotive world and aerospace have always been tightly interconnected, constantly feeding into each other. And Countach's innovative design concept was inspired by the many breakthroughs in space exploration. Its futuristic lines recall the sharp edges of shape shuttles. That's why we decided to interview the world-famous Italian astronaut @mauriziocheli to talk more about the meeting point of these two realms. Because in the same way that the space missions in the last 50 years changed the world,  Countach also redefined what a Super Sports Car could be. 

#Lamborghini #CountachLegacy

The first semester of 2021 saw a record-breaking number of global sales! We registered a 37% increase compared to the same period of 2020 and 6.6% over the first half of 2019, pre-Covid period. The Super SUV Urus was the most sold model (2,796 units), followed by Huracán (1,532) and Aventador (524).

In the 1970s, legendary designer Marcello Gandini worked on Countach, the Super Sports Car that became Automobili Lamborghini's iconic hallmark and radically transformed the automotive industry. Countach's angular, sharp, and space-influenced design was groundbreaking, setting a new standard in automotive design.
